{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"When I first arrived in beautiful Zimbabwe,"},{"time":3000,"text":"it was difficult to understand that 35 percent of the population"},{"time":8000,"text":"is HIV positive."},{"time":11000,"text":"It really wasn't until I was invited to the homes of people"},{"time":15000,"text":"that I started to understand the human toll of the epidemic."},{"time":20000,"text":"For instance, this is Herbert with his grandmother."},{"time":24000,"text":"When I first met him, he was sitting on his grandmother's lap."},{"time":28000,"text":"He has been orphaned, as both of his parents died of AIDS,"},{"time":31000,"text":"and his grandmother took care of him until he too died of AIDS."},{"time":35000,"text":"He liked to sit on her lap"},{"time":37000,"text":"because he said that it was painful for him to lie in his own bed."},{"time":42000,"text":"When she got up to make tea, she placed him in my own lap"},{"time":46000,"text":"and I had never felt a child that was that emaciated."},{"time":53000,"text":"Before I left, I actually asked him if I could get him something."},{"time":57000,"text":"I thought he would ask for a toy, or candy,"},{"time":59000,"text":"and he asked me for slippers,"},{"time":62000,"text":"because he said that his feet were cold."}]},{"cues":[{"time":65000,"text":"This is Joyce who's -- in this picture -- 21."},{"time":68000,"text":"Single mother, HIV positive."},{"time":71000,"text":"I photographed her before and after"},{"time":73000,"text":"the birth of her beautiful baby girl, Issa."},{"time":76000,"text":"And I was last week walking on Lafayette Street in Manhattan"},{"time":79000,"text":"and got a call from a woman who I didn't know,"},{"time":82000,"text":"but she called to tell me that Joyce had passed away"},{"time":85000,"text":"at the age of 23."},{"time":87000,"text":"Joyce's mother is now taking care of her daughter,"},{"time":90000,"text":"like so many other Zimbabwean children"},{"time":92000,"text":"who've been orphaned by the epidemic."},{"time":94000,"text":"So a few of the stories."},{"time":96000,"text":"With every picture,"},{"time":98000,"text":"there are individuals who have full lives"},{"time":103000,"text":"and stories that deserve to be told."},{"time":105000,"text":"All these pictures are from Zimbabwe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":210000,"text":"Chris Anderson: Kirsten, will you just take one minute,"},{"time":212000,"text":"just to tell your own story of how you got to Africa?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":217000,"text":"Kirsten Ashburn: Mmm, gosh."}]},{"cues":[{"time":218000,"text":"CA: Just --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":219000,"text":"KA: Actually, I was working at the time, doing production"},{"time":223000,"text":"for a fashion photographer."},{"time":225000,"text":"And I was constantly reading the New York Times,"},{"time":228000,"text":"and stunned by the statistics, the numbers."},{"time":232000,"text":"It was just frightening."},{"time":234000,"text":"So I quit my job"},{"time":236000,"text":"and decided that that's the subject that I wanted to tackle."},{"time":240000,"text":"And I first actually went to Botswana, where I spent a month --"},{"time":244000,"text":"this is in December 2000 --"},{"time":246000,"text":"then went to Zimbabwe for a month and a half,"},{"time":249000,"text":"and then went back again this March 2002"},{"time":252000,"text":"for another month and a half in Zimbabwe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":255000,"text":"CA: That's an amazing story, thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":257000,"text":"KB: Thanks for letting me show these."}]}]}